<anchor id="keygen_8h_1keygen"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>AXO software use <ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elliptic_Curve_Digital_Signature_Algorithm">Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm (ECDSA)</ulink>. for signing the calculated hash checksum for the data transfer of raw and displacement data via HTTP. On server side these signature and hash checksum will be verified to ensure:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>a) the correctness of the received data</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>b) the validity of the sender identity <linebreak/>
 The software use the <ulink url="https://github.com/Mbed-TLS/mbedtls">mbedtls crypto library</ulink>. For a detailed documentation see <ulink url="https://mbed-tls.readthedocs.io/en/latest/kb/how-to/mbedtls-tutorial/">Mbed TLS tutorial</ulink>. <linebreak/>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>This source code is confidential and proprietary information of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. You may not disclose, copy, or distribute this source code or any part thereof without the explicit permission of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
